modules.description: Provides operations for constructing and manipulating abstract syntax trees, including binary and unary operations, expressions, and declarations. Works with types such as `id`, `exp`, `statement`, and `program` to represent program structure. Used to parse and analyze code, generate intermediate representations, and perform semantic checks.

Provides functions to parse, traverse, and modify OpenQASM abstract syntax trees. Operates on node structures representing quantum circuits, gates, and instructions. Enables transformation of quantum code for analysis or optimization tasks.

Constructs and manipulates abstract syntax trees using types like `id`, `exp`, `statement`, and `program`, supporting binary and unary operations, expressions, and declarations. Enables parsing, analysis, and generation of intermediate representations by transforming and inspecting program structures. Operations include building expressions, annotating statements, and validating semantic constraints. Examples include converting arithmetic expressions into tree structures, extracting identifiers from code, and checking type consistency in declarations.
